Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Kissing men - Decline of violence in history
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b016lggg
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 7 Nov 2011
Laurie Taylor explores Professor Steven Pinker's notion of a decline in human violence with Anthony O'Hear, Professor of Philosophy at the University of Buckingham. Laurie also examines an apparent rise in heterosexual men kissing other men, with Professor Eric Anderson from the University of Winchester. Producer. Chris Wilson. Show less